                     <author key="person_12543979"><supplied>Alexander of Ashby</supplied></author>
                     <title key="work_416">Liber festiualis</title>
                     <rubric>Libellus de Sanctorum miraculis</rubric>
                     <note>A festial in two books, known to be by Alexander Essebiensis (prior of Canons' Ashby), see MS. Bodl. 527, art. 4: but after the Life of st. Guthlac in book 2 the two MSS. differ, MS. Bodl. 527 going on (fol. 125) to st. Marina, and then st. Edward king and confessor, whereas the present MS. (fol. 33) omits Marina.</note>
                  </msItem>
                  <msItem class="#biblia #versus" n="2">
                     <author key="person_61907230"><supplied>Petrus Riga</supplied></author>
                     <title key="work_6589"><supplied>Floridus aspectus</supplied></title>
                     <note><bibl type="repertory"><ref target="http://www.repbib.uni-trier.de/cgi-bin/rebiIndex.tcl?ac=searchlist&amp;tlnr=6822">Stegmüller, <title>Bibl.</title> 6822</ref></bibl></note>
                     <msItem>
                        <locus from="38v">(fol. 38v)</locus>
                        <bibl>(De nativitate Christi)</bibl>
                        <incipit>Nectareum rorem</incipit>
                     </msItem>
